{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.11",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 11,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 11",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 11 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:1",
      "text": "And Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:2",
      "text": "He that speaks much, should also hear on the other side: or does the fluent speaker think himself to be righteous? blessed is the short-lived offspring of woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:3",
      "text": "Be not a speaker of many words; for is there none to answer thee?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:4",
      "text": "For say not, I am pure in my works, and blameless before him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:5",
      "text": "But oh that the Lord would speak to thee, and open his lips with thee!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:6",
      "text": "Then shall he declare to thee the power of wisdom; for it shall be double of that which is with thee: and then shalt thou know, that a just recompence of thy sins has come to thee from the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:7",
      "text": "Wilt thou find out the traces of the Lord? or hast thou come to the end of that which the Almighty has made?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:8",
      "text": "Heaven is high; and what wilt thou do? and there are deeper things than those in hell; what dost thou know?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:9",
      "text": "Or longer than the measure of the earth, or the breadth of the sea.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:10",
      "text": "And if he should overthrow all things, who will say to him, What hast thou done?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:11",
      "text": "For he knows the works of transgressors; and when he sees wickedness, he will not overlook it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:12",
      "text": "But man vainly buoys himself up with words; and a mortal born of woman is like an ass of the desert.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:13",
      "text": "For if thou hast made thine heart pure, and liftest up thine hands towards him;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:14",
      "text": "if there is any iniquity in thy hands, put it far from thee, and let not unrighteousness lodge in thy habitation.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:15",
      "text": "For thus shall thy countenance shine again, as pure water; and thou shalt divest thyself of uncleanness, and shalt not fear.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:16",
      "text": "And thou shalt forget trouble, as a wave that has passed by; and thou shalt not be scared.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:17",
      "text": "And thy prayer shall be as the morning star, and life shall arise to thee as from the noon-day.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:18",
      "text": "And thou shalt be confident, because thou hast hope; and peace shall dawn to thee from out of anxiety and care.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:19",
      "text": "For thou shalt be at ease, and there shall be no one to fight against thee; and many shall charge, and make supplication to thee.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.11.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 11,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 11:20",
      "text": "But safety shall fail them; for their hope is destruction, and the eyes of the ungodly shall waste away.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
